3.28.24  2:27 pm   Which do you prefer - heavy blankets or light blankets?

      i'm holding out for a medium blanket

3.28.24  2:20 pm   Did you ever stop believing in yourself?

      no

3.28.24  1:05 pm   is saying "stay fresh, cheese bags" a good way to leave a room while appearing cool and interesting

      it could work once

3.28.24  1:01 pm   What is your favorite month and why?

      it's a tie between january, march, may, july, august, october, and december. because they have the most days

3.28.24  12:50 pm   how do you select an idea for production 

      i'm really not sure. i just have to decide what i'd like to be stuck with for the rest of my life, or at least it feels that way

3.28.24  12:04 pm   what do you do when you have an appointment, and as the day approaches, it becomes clear that it will be during a time you'd normally be asleep?  do you try to shift things beforehand or set an alarm the day of and deal with the tiredness?

      i don't know any effective way other than waking up by alarm regardless. however what i also know is, as a side effect you will usually find yourself having a great day, once the appointment or obligation is done

3.28.24  11:27 am   recommend me a song ur obsessed w rn

      i'm obsessed with all of them equally. i know that sounds impossible, but here i am, living proof

3.28.24  10:28 am   i want to study physics at university (i'm a senior in highschool) but i would also kinda like studying engineering i guess and i'm to scared that i'm gonna regret wwhichever choice i make especially because physicists are not that valued in my country and idk what to do

      i have no idea how univerties or that sort of higher education works. that whole world and dynamic is very foreign to me. fortunately, it won't prevent you from accomplishing what you really want to

3.28.24  10:22 am   Would you say the more in your head you are, the more miserable you are? And the more you just do, the more regulated you are?

      not quite

      you'll have to put your mind onto something else. your mind has to go somewhere, and when it goes there, it's all there

      why stop there

      walking

3.27.24  5:23 am   why are your videos so weird yet so understandable?

      to prove that that is possible

3.27.24  4:45 am   How do you make an art? I know the short answer is to just do it. But sometimes you try and then life happens and then you need to make money to for the chemicals to stop your body melting and then a kid shows up and then theres back pain and the meat clock goes bad and all the while that unfinished art is just sitting there, taunting me with it's incompleteness. 

      you'll have to reduce the size or complexity of the things you're making, at least for now. the good news is, there's no limit to how complex or uncomplex they can be, and still work just as well

3.27.24  3:34 am   I like your philosophy, or at least I think I do (I haven't worked out if my philosophy agrees with me on that yet) - do you consider yourself philosophically minded?

      i probably am, except as soon as the actual word 'philosophy' is used then that usually ends the party

3.27.24  3:20 am   I have executive dysfunction issues which makes it hard to finish art projects I start. How do you get good at finishing things?

      how about trying some much shorter projects, to make it easier to get some practice

3.27.24  2:40 am   Why do you use the nonsensical American date format (mm/dd/yyyy)?
